The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Punj Lloyd eyes aviation

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Sept. 12: Punj Lloyd today formed a joint venture with Swissport International to enter the domestic aviation market. Swissport International is a global leader in aircraft ground handling industry.

 Under the agreement, Punj Lloyd will hold a 49 per cent stake in the joint venture while the remaining 51 per cent will be with Swissport. 

 This joint venture will enable Punj Lloyd to enter the aviation sector in India, which has robust growth opportunities. We are eagerly looking forward to strengthening our partnership with Swissport into a successful business, Punj Lloyd chairman Atul Punj said. Punj Lloyd is keen to bring world-class ground handling facilities in the country to serve passengers and the growing fleet of domestic carriers, Punj added.

 With India being one of the fastest growing markets in aviation, Swissport sees a strong business potential here.

 Swissports brand and know-how and Punjs local expertise will help the joint venture develop projects in the Indian ground handling sector.

 Owned by Ferrovial of Spain, Swissport International Ltd is a leading European infrastructure and service corporation. It provides ground services to over 70 million passengers and handles 3.2 million tonnes of cargo a year on behalf of around 650 client companies. With a workforce of around 21,000 personnel, Swissport is present at 182 airports in 41 countries. The company clocked consolidated operating revenue of $1.315 billion last year.

 Swissport International president and chief executive Joseph Albon said, This venture is a significant business opportunity that will open up avenues for developing the companys core competencies in ground handling in India and enable us to serve this market with the same high standards that we provide all around the world. 




